---
description: Enforce strict Swift/Flutter parity for Kotlin port
alwaysApply: true
---

# Kotlin Port Priorities

- Do not introduce hardcoded values or logic in Kotlin unless they are already hardcoded in Swift/Flutter.
- Source data from the same catalogs/resources used by Swift/Flutter whenever available.
- Follow Swift/Flutter architecture, contracts, layering, and behavior 1:1 by default.
- Deviation is allowed only when platform constraints make it necessary; call out each deviation and why.
- If requirements are ambiguous or a change is risky, ask before implementing.
- Prefer evidence-based fixes from reference files over speculative rewrites.
- Keep app layer thin and preserve library ownership of transport/mock/decode logic.
- After substantial changes, run build/tests and state exactly what was verified.
